Chat-Based AI Agent: Full Stack Implementation

This document outlines the complete full-stack implementation for the RAG-based AI Agent, combining a React frontend with a Python (FastAPI) and PostgreSQL (pgvector) backend.

1. System Architecture

Frontend: React (Tailwind CSS, Lucide Icons)

Backend: Python 3.11+, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy

Database: PostgreSQL with the pgvector extension

AI Models: OpenAI gpt-4o (chat) and text-embedding-3-small (embeddings)

2. Backend Implementation (Python / FastAPI)

This is the core backend logic. It handles the Priority Context Engine, generates embeddings, queries the vector database, and streams the context to OpenAI.

